Jenkinsfile : Pipeline as a code

Step 1 Start Jenkins
Step 2 Install Pipeline Plugin
Step 3 Create a new job (type: Pipeline)
Step 4 Create Jenkinsfile in Pipeline section (Configure -> Pipeline)
       i.e select definition = pipeline script, script type: <helloworld>
Step 5 Run and check the output


How to get jenkinsfile from Git SCM

Step 1 : Create a new job or use existing job (type: Pipeline)
Step 2 : Create a repository in GitHub
Step 3 : Add Jenkinsfile in the repository
Step 4 : Under Jenkins job ＞ Pipeline section ＞ Select Definition = Pipeline script from SCM,
         SCM = Git, Select Credentials, select 'Branches to build' to main or master (main in our case)
Step 5 : Add repository and jenkinsfile location in the job under Pipeline section
Step 6 : Save & Run (Build)
